	   <tr><td colspan=2>I got this for my Shaman Alternate Character today. Here's how I got the Bear. I bound my Druid by the tunnel entrance and then killed the wandering Ice Bone PH's. I left then and did some other hunting by porting out of the cave. Over a week and a half period I gated back to the cave to check if the bear was up. I also checked to see if wandering Icebones were up. Always there were wandering IB's, so I killed them again. I stayed at the entrance, and nailed the IB's as they walked past there. You can see the Lich walk by from there too, so its a safe spot. Somewhere someone said the bear is a 8 hour spawn, and to check back 8 hours after killing an IB. THIS IS WRONG! You need to get back into the cave to check on the bear because he spawns from 61/2 to 81/2 hours after the PH's are killed. Waiting 8 hours is the reason so many people say they just went to the cave and found the bear. Or that they were hunting mammoths and a Ranger buddy saw the bear on track so they went down and got it. Some poor smuck killed the Icebones and then logged on 8 hours later to find nothing, because the Bear had already been killed. My Bear spawned 7 hours after I killed the IB's. I stood at the entrance to wait for him, and it took 25 minutes for the bear to work its way through its route to where I was waiting. Twenty minutes into my wait a Frigging Ranger and his Shaman buddy show up, run past me and start scouting the caves. I stayed put close enought to the&nbsp;&nbsp;first intersection where I could see anything walking past east to west in the first intrsection from the entrance of the tunnels. The Ranger didn't find the bear, Cause I saw it walk through the intersection from a clockwise direction. I ran up to the intersection, snared the bear and kited up and down the tunnel from the Intersection to the Ice Goblin Diver near the water. It took I beleive ( I lost count) five Combusts and a Creeping Crud. The Bear took max damage (180) on every cast of Combust but for one cast where it did 65 damage. I had 4 bubbles of health left and 1 bubble of manna. I seriously think I may have quit the game if the Ranger had got my bear, and I have to say to him is: kill some PH's you lazy KSer. Hope this helps everyone who going to attemp this very boring and stupid quest.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
