	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97964949522685><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=search.shtml?id=3714&mid=97964949522685>Skinny on the Glacier Bear</a> <a id=fs8 href=search.shtml?id=3714&mid=97964949522685#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=18613><span id= >Maruwindl</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>7 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jan 16th 12:53 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.25]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have killed him now twice in the last few weeks.&nbsp;&nbsp;A friend of mine killed him 5 times in 2 weeks.  Getting him is hard but here are some easy steps to do it.  (It's best to do it while you are around level 30, gives you something to do in Everfrost).<br><br>1. Make sure you know where to look for him and know his path... finding maps of the caves and his path isn't hard.  (Also, make sure to know the path of the Lich and where the other necro NPC is located before you run around like a bratty kid at Chucky Cheese)<br><br>2. Make sure you either have track, sense animal, or someone who can that you can TRUST.  This animal is too hard to get to leave to chance and the helm is worth too much to get it Yoinked by someone you thought was helping you.  Just going down into the caves to the ice skeleton altar and using sense animal or track is good enough.  No need to search his entire route.  If he's up, you'll see him.  (If you do NOT have a way to track, simply go to ice boned hut and wait if you think he's up, he comes to that location and stands there during his route)<br><br>3. Make sure you have all the spells you need up, or that you have someone by to heal you.  (Note: ice or cold spells are no good, so don't waste the mana)  He really can't take disease and poison spells though so pile em up.  Fire is probably good too.  He isn't much harder than the average wooly mammoth (HP-wise).<br><br>4. Have something to do.  That is why it's important to be around level 30.  You can kill mammoths and gain exp and still go down every 7-8 hours or so.  Or wait until high 40's and kill Ice Giants.  Just as long as you have something to do.  (And find out about place holders so you know what to kill to get him to spawn!)<br><br>5. MOST importantly:  1) ANY TIME they announce the servers coming down (especially if it's only for a few minutes)  RUN down to the caves and CAMP there (make sure you can actually camp so you are saved there.... wouldn't be good to be disconnected and pop back on to find yourself tangoing with the Lich)  When they reopen the servers you have a 33% chance he's up, so stay alert for the servers coming back up too.  OR<br>2) Play at night when few others are on.  That way you can hold the spawn from out on the tundra and you don't have to sit down in the caves picking off stationary ice bones for kicks.<br><br>6.  LAST of all, be smart.  Don't get all excited when you see him and jump him with half health and mana.  Take your time.  If someone jumps in and tries to KS him, petition.  (It IS only a game... oops BLASPHEMY hehehe)  It is also possible to pull him out onto the tundra (he will come up through holes in the ice) but he's a fast swimmer so be careful.  And, sweet God, don't let Tundra Jack KS him...<br><br>(Note:  you COULD always kill the placeholder and then camp, logging back in every 7-8 hours to either get the bear or kill placeholders again, but i wouldn't advise it.  Either you'll miss him altogether or you'll pop up and find someone else camping him. It's happened to me and do you think they'll actually believe that you are camping him like that?  LOL)<br><br>Anyway, good luck and hope i've helped,<br><br>  Maruwindl Frostbane (Knights of Templar, E'ci)<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
