	   <tr><td colspan=2>The real scoop is that the lich is KOS to everyone, be it storyline wise or FA quest wise. To make FA a very guild based quest, Verant made it necessary for the lich to be charmed by an enchanter or necro so that u can talk to him. But I think he stops being KOS if u return the phylactery artifact which stores its soul. In the story, Miragul's heart has grown as cold as the frigid plains, that is why he likes that place so much, with no one there to bother him, he thirsts for knowledge, that is when he has decided to return to Paineel to see if the heretics have found a way to become immortal. Although they did not, Miragul played along with them in raising an army of undead to attack the good city of Erudin while experimenting with himself all the while. He realises that the undead ceases to age and wants to be like them. He returned to his chamber with an artifact called the phylactery he stole from the heretics and transferred his soul into the Phylactery as soon as his experiment began. The experiment was successful, but Miragul realised one glaring strategic flaw, he had forgotten to place a step in the experiment to transfer his soul back into the lifeless corpse of his former self, which is now an undead and retains all of its knowledge, without the soul. Miragul could do nothing except scream in anguish. In the FA quest, the phylactery ended up with the oracle of K'ar'non (not Ak'ar non the gnome city) the guy u kill for the oracle robe. They also say that if u perform the quest of Azraax's (spelling) legacy quest to obtain the mantle of souls, u can raise faction with Miragul greatly. U can also see in Caster's realm a screenshot of FA quest when the lich is back to his Erudite self, the players hailed him and he said 'leave me be, worm'<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
